  "description": [
    "JLLes County HERALD Published by the Holmes County Publishing Company at 200 Tchula Street Lexington Mississippi Entered at the Postoffice at Lexington Mississippi as Second Class mail under the Act of Congress of March 3 1879 Subscription rates for Holmes and adjoining counties 300 per year six months 200 elsewhere 400 per year PAUL TARDY Editor ALLIE S TARDY Associate Editor Notes and quotes of a feminine nature By Allie Tardy Irrespective of political affini ty religion color race or sta tion in life we have this week been a nation united in grief From California to Maine and from Michigan tto Mississippi wo have united in sorrow and prayer Bitterness was put aside for grief criticism was forgotten as heads were bowed in prayer and rebukes were few as a na tion and a world stood silent in tribute to a fallen leader We have run the gamut of emo tions of human kind in this week that should have been one of Thanksgiving Disbelief shock horror fear reprehension guilt anger revulsion grief sorrow and loneliness have assailed us each in their turn as we have had to face the reality of such a thing occuring in our nation"
  ],
